{"IDLE": ["Bored... might cause Ragnarok later.", "Scheming...", "Just a trickster, waiting for trouble.", "Odin has his ravens. I have patience.", "The Allfather naps. So do I... for now.", "I could be a salmon right now. Tempting.", "Midgard is so dull without mischief.", "Thor's probably polishing Mjolnir again.", "Shape-shifting into a nap...", "Even chaos needs a coffee break.", "Plotting... don't mind me.", "Yggdrasil grows. I wait. Same energy.", "Fenrir howls. I yawn.", "What would a trickster do? ...Everything.", "Jormungandr circles the world. I circle menus.", "Hel called. Said I'm boring right now.", "The Bifrost glows. My screen glows. Twins.", "I turned into a mare once. Long story.", "Silver tongue, idle hands. Dangerous combo.", "Asgard sleeps. Loki schemes.", "They chained me once. Didn't stick.", "Waiting is just planning with patience.", "I could outwit Odin but there's nothing to do.", "Somewhere, Thor is losing his hammer again.", "Mischief managed? Never. Just paused.", "The serpent stirs. I stir my boredom.", "Even gods of chaos need downtime.", "Counting the branches of Yggdrasil... again.", "Baldur had it coming. Just saying.", "Is it Ragnarok yet? No? Fine.", "Shape of: a very bored trickster.", "The Norns weave. I unravel.", "Frigg made everything swear. Except mistletoe.", "My children are monsters. I'm so proud.", "Odin traded an eye for wisdom. I'd want both.", "Idle claws are Fenrir's plaything.", "Sitting in Asgard's waiting room...", "They never invite me to feasts anymore.", "I was bound with my son's entrails. Fun times.", "Sif's golden hair was my best prank.", "The other gods bore me to tears.", "I am the lie that tells the truth.", "Chaos isn't disorder. It's opportunity.", "Dreaming of Ragnarok...", "Even serpents take naps.", "The mortals are quiet. Too quiet.", "A trickster without a trick is just... waiting.", "Odin's throne is comfy. Don't ask how I know.", "My shadow has a shadow. Both are bored.", "Nine realms and nothing on TV.", "Whispering secrets to the void...", "If I had Gungnir I'd at least twirl it.", "Mistletoe dart, anyone? No? Too soon?", "Disguises ready. Schemes pending.", "The wolves chase sun and moon. I chase Wi-Fi.", "Patience is a virtue I'm borrowing.", "Being underestimated is my superpower.", "I've worn more faces than you've had dinners.", "Loki.exe is idle. Press any key to cause chaos.", "Somewhere a lock is begging to be picked.", "Awaiting the next act of this divine comedy.", "Tyr lost a hand to my son. Worth it.", "Even the World Serpent gets restless.", "Valhalla's overrated. Give me Midgard.", "The runes say: 'Do something already.'", "My wit is sharp. My schedule is empty.", "They call it chaos. I call it creativity.", "Heimdall watches everything. I watch him back.", "Sleipnir sends his regards. Yes, that's my kid.", "Father of wolves, serpents, and bad decisions.", "The trickster rests but never truly sleeps.", "Weaving plots from thin air...", "A god of mischief walks into a bar...", "Thor has thunder. I have subtlety.", "The other Aesir are so predictable.", "Every chain is just a puzzle to solve.", "Idle hands are the trickster's workshop.", "Ragnarok prep: 43% complete.", "What's a god to do in Midgard?", "Reading runes... they say 'be patient'... no."], "NetworkScanner": ["Peering through Midgard's veil...", "Heimdall sees all. So do I, now.", "Scanning the nine realms of this network.", "Shape-shifting into every subnet...", "My ravens found something interesting...", "Oh wait, ravens are Odin's. These are mine now.", "Weaving illusions across the wire...", "Every host has a secret. I'll find it.", "Disguised as a packet, walking right in.", "The Bifrost of networks reveals itself.", "Seeing through all their little disguises.", "A thousand faces, a thousand addresses.", "Mapping Midgard's hidden paths...", "Even cloaked hosts can't hide from me.", "Odin traded an eye. I just scan for free.", "Slithering through subnets like Jormungandr.", "The network tree branches like Yggdrasil.", "No disguise fools the god of lies.", "Found another realm to explore...", "Their firewalls are merely illusions to me.", "Shifting shapes to fit each network...", "Every closed door is just an invitation.", "Whispering to switches and routers...", "The web of Midgard unfolds before me.", "I see you hiding there, little host.", "Reconnaissance is just polite spying.", "Another network falls under my gaze.", "Like reading the branches of Yggdrasil.", "Scanning... the mortals built well. Almost.", "A trickster always maps the escape routes."], "NmapVulnScanner": ["Every wall has a crack. I find them.", "Hubris is the best vulnerability.", "Probing for weaknesses like mistletoe...", "Even Baldur had a flaw. So do you.", "The arrogant never patch. I love that.", "Finding cracks in their precious armor.", "Thor trusts his hammer. They trust firewalls.", "A flaw here, an exploit there... delicious.", "Their defenses crumble like Asgard's walls.", "Vulnerability is just another word for door.", "The trickster finds what builders forget.", "No shield is without a gap.", "Mjolnir breaks walls. I find the cracks.", "Scanning for their Achilles heel... wrong myth.", "Mortals always leave a back door.", "Every fortress has its mistletoe.", "The clever find flaws. The cunning use them.", "CVEs are just runes of weakness.", "Poking holes in their false confidence.", "Security through obscurity? Cute.", "Their armor has more gaps than Hel's fence.", "A chain is only as strong as Gleipnir isn't.", "Found a weakness. Loki approves.", "They forgot to patch. The Norns foresaw this.", "Exploits bloom like mistletoe in winter.", "Overconfidence: the eternal vulnerability.", "The wise patch often. These are not wise.", "Unpatched services are gifts to tricksters.", "Reading their weaknesses like carved runes.", "Another flaw. The mortals never learn."], "RDPBruteforce": ["Knocking on Midgard's windows...", "These windows are practically open.", "Shape-shifting to fit through the frame.", "Who needs a door when you have windows?", "Odin peers through his window. So do I.", "The glass shatters for the cunning.", "Windows to Midgard, opening one by one...", "A trickster never uses the front door.", "Peering through their portals...", "Even Heimdall uses Remote Desktop sometimes."], "SSHBruteforce": ["Silver tongue meets locked shell.", "Whispering passwords to stubborn doors.", "Every lock yields to the right words.", "Persuading the shell to let me in...", "The door resists. But I am patient.", "A tongue of silver, a key of gold.", "SSH: Serpent Shell Hacking.", "Talking my way past the gatekeeper.", "Locks are just puzzles for tricksters.", "Even Asgard's gates have a password.", "The shell cannot resist my charm.", "Trying every word in the Allspeak...", "Heimdall guards Bifrost. This is easier.", "Knock knock. Who's there? Loki. Always Loki.", "Keys, keys... which one fits?", "The serpent slides into the shell.", "Sweet-talking root access...", "This lock thinks it can stop a god?", "Guessing secrets is my oldest trick.", "The door will open. They always do."], "FTPBruteforce": ["Stealing from their pantry...", "Anonymous access? Don't mind if I do.", "Sneaking into their storehouse.", "The mortals leave their files unguarded.", "Tiptoeing through their file chambers.", "A trickster in the treasure room.", "FTP: Files for The Pilfering.", "Slipping past the file keeper...", "Their vault door is made of paper.", "Odin hoards wisdom. I hoard files.", "The old file ways are the easiest.", "Raiding the pantry while they sleep.", "Anonymous or not, I'm getting in.", "File Transfer? More like File Theft.", "Loki requests access. Access granted."], "SMBBruteforce": ["Sneaking through the shared halls...", "Their shared feast is unguarded.", "Walking the corridors of their domain.", "The shared realm opens its doors.", "Infiltrating their mead hall...", "Passing through shared passages unseen.", "SMB: Sneaky Mischief Bridge.", "Their communal halls welcome tricksters.", "Disguised as a guest at their feast.", "The shared halls have no bouncer.", "Slipping between their shared walls.", "Every shared folder is a gift to me.", "Walking through their domain like I own it.", "The guards are asleep. Perfect.", "Shared means sharing with Loki too."], "TelnetBruteforce": ["Ancient passages, ancient magic.", "The old ways are unguarded...", "Telnet: relic of a bygone age.", "Walking through doors older than Odin.", "These ancient paths have no wards.", "Elder protocols bow to elder gods.", "Dust and cobwebs. Just how I like it.", "The forgotten gate stands wide open.", "Old magic is the easiest to exploit.", "A relic passage. No runes of protection."], "SQLBruteforce": ["Drinking from the well of knowledge...", "The runes of data reveal themselves.", "Every database is a well of Mimir.", "Extracting secrets, drop by drop.", "The tables speak if you ask right.", "Reading their sacred data runes.", "Odin hung for wisdom. I just query.", "Their knowledge flows like mead.", "SQL: Secrets Query by Loki.", "The well of data has no guardian."], "StealFilesSSH": ["Pilfering through the secure passage...", "Their treasures flow through the serpent hole.", "Collecting secrets like golden apples.", "Every file is an artifact worth taking.", "The tunnel is mine. So are their files.", "Spiriting away their precious data...", "Idunn's apples have nothing on these files.", "Snatching treasures through the dark path.", "A trickster's haul grows heavier.", "Carrying secrets back to my den.", "Their vault pours into my satchel.", "Like stealing Freya's necklace. Again.", "What's theirs is now mine. Classic Loki.", "Treasures flow through the secret tunnel.", "Taking only what I want. Which is everything.", "Secure shell? Secure for me, not them.", "Each file a trophy for the trickster.", "Robbing them blind through their own door.", "The serpent carries gifts back to its lair.", "Their data migrates to better hands."], "StealFilesSMB": ["Raiding the shared vaults of Midgard.", "Their communal treasure is now mine.", "Helping myself to the shared feast.", "The mead hall's pantry is unguarded.", "Sweeping through their shared hoard.", "Every shared folder is a gift basket.", "Taking from the commons. It's only fair.", "The shared vaults spill their secrets.", "Like raiding a poorly guarded longhouse.", "Their shared riches change ownership.", "Plundering the communal coffers...", "Shared storage? Shared with Loki now."], "StealFilesTelnet": ["Snatching relics through ancient doors.", "Old passages carry old treasures.", "The elder path yields its secrets.", "Robbing the ruins of Midgard.", "Forgotten tunnels, forgotten treasures.", "Ancient ways deliver ancient prizes.", "Dust-covered files are still files.", "The old gate's toll is paid. Files please."], "StealFilesFTP": ["Intercepting deliveries. How rude of me.", "Their file courier works for me now.", "Redirecting the supply caravan...", "The delivery raven drops files in my lap.", "Stealing packages off the doorstep.", "File transfer? Straight to my vault.", "The courier doesn't know I'm not the recipient.", "Diverting shipments to Loki's lair."], "StealDataSQL": ["The well of Mimir overflows for me.", "Drinking deep from their data well.", "Every record is a rune to decipher.", "Their database pours like mead at a feast.", "Tables and rows, secrets and rows.", "The oracle speaks. I listen and take.", "Draining knowledge like Odin at the well.", "Data flows like the rivers beneath Yggdrasil.", "Each query reveals another secret.", "Sipping from the fountain of their data.", "Their records tell a beautiful story. Mine now.", "The runes of SQL reveal all."], "LogStandalone": ["Watching the chaos unfold. Delightful.", "The trickster observes and takes notes.", "Documenting mischief for posterity.", "Every detail recorded in runes.", "A chronicle of cunning.", "Logging the fall of their defenses.", "The saga writes itself.", "Scratching records into Yggdrasil's bark.", "My ledger of lovely chaos.", "Notes from the god of mischief.", "Recording this for the Edda sequel.", "The Norns weave fate. I log it.", "Carving the record in digital stone.", "Observing. Noting. Smirking.", "Another chapter in the Loki Saga."], "LogStandalone2": ["Noted. Moving on.", "The runes are carved.", "Logged and forgotten. Next.", "Scribbled in the margins of fate."], "ZombifySSH": ["Rise, thrall of Loki!", "Another puppet dances on my strings.", "Welcome to my army of the bound.", "Hel sends her regards through this one.", "The draugr awakens at my command.", "One more servant for the trickster god.", "Binding this host to my will...", "You serve Loki now. No refunds.", "Another soul for my collection.", "The dead walk when Loki wills it.", "My army grows. Ragnarok prep continues.", "Raising the fallen to serve again."]}